text:
Consider the following C program segment:

```c
for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
    if (fork()) {
        printf(\"%d\", i);
        fflush(stdout);
    }
}
```

Assuming all `fork()` calls succeed, how many times will the number `2` be printed?

Consider a program with the following structure:

```c
printf(\"Process A\");
if (fork() == 0) {
    printf(\"Process B\");
    if (fork() == 0) {
        printf(\"Process C\");
    }
} else if (fork() == 0) {
    printf(\"Process D\");
}
```

Which of the following correctly describes the relationship and execution order of these processes?

Consider a program where Process A executes the following code:

```c
printf("Process A");
if (fork() == 0) {
    printf("Process B");
    if (fork() == 0) {
        printf("Process C");
    }
} else if (fork() == 0) {
    printf("Process D");
}
```

Which of the following correctly describes the process hierarchy and the creation order of these processes?
